No, I/you/he etc. can't.

ćwiczenie 8:
Ułóż prawdziwe zdania, używając can lub can't.
1. An artist /paint pictures
An artist can paint pictures.
2 A cat / fly
A cat can't fly.
3 A monkey / climb trees
3 A monkey can climb trees.
4 A leopard / run fast
4 A leopard can run fast.
5 A pilot / fly an aeroplane
5 A pilot can fly an aeroplane.
6 A dog/ talk
6 A dog can't talk.
7 A fish / walk
7 A fish can't walk.
8 An elephant / fly
8 An elephant can't fly.
9 A baker / make bread
9 A baker can make bread.
10 A hamster / ride a bicycle
10 A hamster can't ride a bicycle.

